{"index": 34, "en_name": "Epistle of Jeremiah", "local_name": "", "chapters": [], "metadata": [{"title": "Author", "content_parts": [{"style": "NONE", "text": "—Jeremiah the prophet"}]}, {"title": "Date", "content_parts": [{"style": "NONE", "text": "—Written in the aftermath of the sack of Jerusalem (597 BC) and the exile to Babylon of her leaders, probably from Egypt."}]}, {"title": "Major Theme", "content_parts": [{"style": "NONE", "text": "—"}, {"style": "ITALIC", "text": "Beware of idols!"}, {"style": "NONE", "text": "Beware of idols!"}]}, {"title": "Background", "content_parts": [{"style": "NONE", "text": "—The epistle is a diatribe against the sin of idolatry as represented by the Baal cult."}, {"style": "NONE", "text": " Jeremiah wrote to the Israelites to exhort and warn them to be free of a sin that must have been on the increase at this time."}, {"style": "NONE", "text": " Because the epistle has very little historical information, it became timeless and was used by certain Church Fathers to combat pagan errors and superstitions practiced in their own day."}, {"style": "NONE", "text": " The epistle conveys a message that heresy and false ideas about God are both ridiculous and untenable."}]}, {"title": "Outline", "content_parts": [{"style": "NONE", "text": "Outline"}], "list": [[{"style": "NONE", "text": "Idols adorned like people (vv."}, {"style": "CROSS_REF", "text": "7–14", "target": {"href": "EpistleofJeremiah.html#EpJer_vchap1-7", "book_file": "EpistleofJeremiah", "chapter": 1, "verse": 7}}, {"style": "NONE", "text": ")"}], [{"style": "NONE", "text": "Uselessness and helplessness of idols (vv."}, {"style": "CROSS_REF", "text": "15–24", "target": {"href": "EpistleofJeremiah.html#EpJer_vchap1-15", "book_file": "EpistleofJeremiah", "chapter": 1, "verse": 15}}, {"style": "NONE", "text": ")"}], [{"style": "NONE", "text": "Idols cannot move (vv."}, {"style": "CROSS_REF", "text": "25–28", "target": {"href": "EpistleofJeremiah.html#EpJer_vchap1-25", "book_file": "EpistleofJeremiah", "chapter": 1, "verse": 25}}, {"style": "NONE", "text": ")"}], [{"style": "NONE", "text": "Idols cannot repay good or evil; they cannot give wealth, save, or heal (vv."}, {"style": "CROSS_REF", "text": "29–39", "target": {"href": "EpistleofJeremiah.html#EpJer_vchap1-29", "book_file": "EpistleofJeremiah", "chapter": 1, "verse": 29}}, {"style": "NONE", "text": ")"}], [{"style": "NONE", "text": "The Chaldeans even bring shame upon their own idols (vv."}, {"style": "CROSS_REF", "text": "40–44", "target": {"href": "EpistleofJeremiah.html#EpJer_vchap1-40", "book_file": "EpistleofJeremiah", "chapter": 1, "verse": 40}}, {"style": "NONE", "text": ")"}], [{"style": "NONE", "text": "Idols are the works of human hands (vv."}, {"style": "CROSS_REF", "text": "45–52", "target": {"href": "EpistleofJeremiah.html#EpJer_vchap1-45", "book_file": "EpistleofJeremiah", "chapter": 1, "verse": 45}}, {"style": "NONE", "text": ")"}], [{"style": "NONE", "text": "Idols are powerless (vv."}, {"style": "CROSS_REF", "text": "53–57", "target": {"href": "EpistleofJeremiah.html#EpJer_vchap1-53", "book_file": "EpistleofJeremiah", "chapter": 1, "verse": 53}}, {"style": "NONE", "text": ")"}], [{"style": "NONE", "text": "Idols cannot be compared to the sun, moon, stars, animals, etc."}, {"style": "NONE", "text": " (vv."}, {"style": "CROSS_REF", "text": "58–69", "target": {"href": "EpistleofJeremiah.html#EpJer_vchap1-58", "book_file": "EpistleofJeremiah", "chapter": 1, "verse": 58}}, {"style": "NONE", "text": ")"}], [{"style": "NONE", "text": "Idols compared to scarecrows, brambles, and a corpse (vv."}, {"style": "CROSS_REF", "text": "70–73", "target": {"href": "EpistleofJeremiah.html#EpJer_vchap1-70", "book_file": "EpistleofJeremiah", "chapter": 1, "verse": 70}}, {"style": "NONE", "text": ")"}]]}]}